The People;’s Democratic Party (PDP) candidate for the Isoko Federal Constituency seat in the House of Representatives, Pastor Engr Jonathan Ukodhiko has congratulated former Nigerian Vice President, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar on his emergence as the presidential candidate of the party for the 2023 general election. Alhaji Abubakar who polled 371 votes, defeated his closest rival and Governor of Rivers State, Barrister Nyesom Wike who had 237 votes at the just-concluded National Convention of the party held at Abuja, the Nation’s Federal Capital Territory. Ukodhiko in a statement on Sunday at his Otor-Igho country home in Isoko North Local Government Area of Delta State commended the leaders, stakeholders and national delegates of the party to the Convention for the peaceful, transparent and orderliness of the electoral process recorded at the National Convention. -Advertisement- According to him, “with what we have seen yesterday (Saturday) at the National Convention of our great party, the PDP in Abuja, it goes to show truly that there’s a future for democracy in Nigeria, and that we are very capable and more determined to peacefully elect our leaders without fear or favour, and violation of the governing laws of the country, and democratic norms. The PDP is exemplary in this regard. “Our party, the PDP remains not just the most ideal and reformed political party for our nation but the most viable political platform for the rebirth of our nation, Nigeria. It is a pan-Nigerian party which has in its name, the two ideal components of democracy, that is, “people” and “democracy “ Ukodhiko expressed optimism that, with the emergence of Alhaji Atiku Abubakar, the nation would be rescued and reinvented. “With Atiku Abubakar who is a major restructuring campaigner, a former custom boss, a private sector participant and former Vice President of the country at the helms of affairs of the nation as president, our country will witness a national transformation that is direly needed to turn around the fortunes of our country. “I once again congratulate His Excellency, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar on his emergence as the presidential flag-bearer of our party, PDP, and I am expressing my willingness to work together with him at the Federal Level in Abuja to ensure a more united, safer and economically buoyant Nigeria once elected“ POLL The PDP House of Representatives candidate for Isoko Federal Constituency, Engr Jonathan Ukodhiko appealed to all presidential aspirants to close ranks and throw their weights behind Alhaji Atiku Abubakar to run a well-organized campaign to all nooks and crannies of the nation with the sole purpose to form the next Federal Government that would restore hope to the people of Nigeria, and ensure that Nigeria remains the leader and pride of Africa and Black people all over the world”, he added.